# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cloud storage for published biodatas (the /name share links).
#
# In LOCAL development you can leave these unset — the app falls back to a JSON
# file store under .data/ so publishing works without any setup.
#
# In PRODUCTION, add a Redis store and these get injected automatically:
#   1. Deploy the app to Vercel.
#   2. Vercel dashboard → Storage → "Marketplace Database Providers" →
#      add "Upstash for Redis" (free tier) and connect it to this project.
#   3. Vercel injects KV_REST_API_URL and KV_REST_API_TOKEN for you. Redeploy.
#
# (UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL / _TOKEN are also accepted.)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

KV_REST_API_URL=
KV_REST_API_TOKEN=
